name: Wildlife Enforcement Monitoring System (WEMS)
location: AIT Solutions, AIT, 58 Moo 9, km. 42 Paholyothin Road, Kloung Nueng, Khlong Luang, Pathumthani , Pathumthani 12120, TH
about: WEMS initiative was developed by United Nations University (UNU) in 2005, to address challenges in wildlife law enforcement information collection, compilation, and sharing process. WEMS database is designed to cater national government‚Äôs needs in managing information and reporting them and support them in accomplishing national targets and fulfilling international commitments under MEAs and for SDGs. WEMS is a web-based information system with GIS functionality able to identify trading routes and provide location analysis of illegal trading and poaching of wildlife species. The data entered is stored in the format of Interpol eco-message providing real time query based on computer analysis by relevant enforcement authorities; thereby providing a common information sharing platform between national enforcement agencies attending to wildlife crime within the country and with regional networks. WEMS initiative has two established regional centers: WEMS Asia at the Asian Institute of Technology via AIT Solutions to pilot project in Asia and WEMS Africa implemented through the Lusaka Agreement Task Force (LATF) with Congo-Brazzaville, Kenya, Tanzania ,Uganda, Liberia and Zambia.
specialties: conservation , wildlife, sustainable development , and innovative technologies

We now play in the South Australian National Premier League (NPL SA). City was founded and is primarily followed by people of Italian heritage, originally called Juventus from 1946 to 1966. In 1966 we became Adelaide Juventus, and in 1977 Adelaide City, when Frank Lister captained the team in the inaugural Phillips NSL competition. The club is one of the biggest across the NPL in Australia and arguably the most prominent in South Australia. Several past and present players, coaches, and administrators of the Black and White have been inducted into the Football South Australia Hall of Fame. Our impact also extends to the national stage. We have provided a pathway for several past and present Socceroos, Matildas, and a plethora of the best players to play in national competitions across Australia. Adelaide City also boasts a strong women's program. We pride ourselves on offering the best facilities, quality coaching, and dedicated volunteers for all of our junior and senior programs.

The programme has been a major success, allowing immigrant investors from all over the world to pursue \"the American dream\" while also generating billions of dollars for the US economy. The initiative was temporarily halted in June 2021 after failing to receive unanimous authorisation in Congress. Many investors were placed in limbo as a result of this. However, President Biden re-authorised the programme to resume operations on March 15, 2022. about: Knust-SBD Pte Ltd‚Äôs parent company Schoeller-Bleckmann Oilfield Equipment (SBO AG) is a leading worldwide supplier of non magnetic steels and drill string components to the MWD, LWD and Directional Drilling industries. Our corporate office and main manufacturing facility is located in Ternitz, Austria. SBO has decades of experience in the manufacture of specialty steels and directional drilling tools and components. SBO has an outstanding reputation for the manufacture and supply of non magnetic MWD, LWD and drill string components which is based upon our continuous research and development of high strength non magnetic steels and our proven capabilities in precision machining. Our precision machining facilities are located in Ternitz Austria, Chesterfield UK, Houston Texas, Neuvo Leon Mexico, Binh Duong Vietnam as well as in Singapore when Knust SBO Far East was established in 2012 to meet our customers requirements for precision tools, components and laser overlay products in the Far East. With the acquisition of Darron Oil Tools in 2002, SBO expanded its product range to include the manufacture of drilling tools and offers a wide range of repair and maintenance services for oilfield equipment. In our continuing efforts to service the needs of our customers we have established a worldwide network of facilities capable of manufacturing, repairing and maintaining drilling tools. In addition to Knust-SBD‚Äôs facilities in Singapore other facilities are located in Aberdeen Scotland, Louisiana USA, Dubai UAE, Brazil, Nisku Canada, and Russia. In 2016 Knust SBO Far East Pte Ltd and SB Darron Pte Ltd were merged creating Knust-SBD Pte Ltd integrating our precision manufacturing and oilfield services capabilities in Singapore. SBO is committed to producing products that meet the highest industry and customer quality standards and as such all manufacturing facilities are certified to both API and ISO quality standards

name: The National Trust of Western Australia
location: 4 Havelock St, Perth, Western Australia 6005, AU
about:
The National Trust of Western Australia works to raise knowledge, awareness, understanding and commitment to Western Australia‚Äôs natural, Aboriginal and historic heritage. The Trust achieves this objective through the conservation and interpretation of heritage places it manages on behalf of the community and government of Western Australia, and through its education and learning programs.

The National Trust of Western Australia was established in Western Australia in 1959 by a group of concerned citizens who identified the need to promote heritage conservation. This group grew rapidly and included some of the most prominent citizens in the State. Some five years later an Act of Parliament was passed in the State Parliament which formally established the Trust as an independent community based organisation.
specialties: Heritage Services, Cultural Tourism, Heritage Conservation, and Community Engagement

name: California National University
location: 18520 Hawthorne Blvd, First Floor, Torrance, CA 90504, US
about: California National University (CNU) was founded in January 1993 in recognition of the need for working adults to meet contemporary challenges to re-think and re-tool. From the beginning it has been CNU's intent to provide quality degree programs in a flexible environment. This goal has been accomplished by adopting an innovative approach to traditional education; combining self-study with direct personal contact and technology. A unique aspect to CNU programs is the one-on-one instruction students receive from a distinguished national faculty. Although the University has taken advantage of advancements in technology to improve instruction, technology is regarded as an enhancement rather than a replacement for good teaching and relevant content. Students enjoy an educational climate that is typical of one found on a small traditional campus. This is made possible at a distance through a centralized Learning Network; emphasizing committed student service and open communication. CNU is one of the only universities that offers an accredited Bachelor and Master of Science in Engineering completely online! CNU is Accredited by the Accrediting Commission of the Distance Education and Training Council www.detc.org. Over nine programs to choose from including: - Bachelor of Science in Engineering - Bachelor of Quality Assurance Science - Bachelor of Computer Science - Bachelor of Business Administration - Master of Business Administration (MBA) - Master of Science in Engineering - Master of Engineering Management - Master of Human R - esources Management We also offer certification programs in: - Six SIgma Green and Black Belt - Human Resources Management
specialties: College of Engineering, College of Quality and Engineering Management, College of Business Administration, Six Sigma Green Belt Certification, Six Sigma Black Belt Certification, QAS 501 Six Sigma Green and Black Belt, and Human Resources (HR) Certification

updates: [{"comments_count":2,"likes_count":75,"text":"With the help of our partner PANAM Engineers LTD and the ingenuity of our members, we have successfully hotfired our new vertical system, Eureka-2. We are excited for the future of this partnership and will share more details of our work together soon. Thank you to PANAM Engineers LTD, and as always, blue skies and bright stars!","time":"2mo","title":"Space Enterprise at Berkeley"},{"comments_count":3,"likes_count":100,"text":"WOW! On December 3rd, Space Enterprise at Berkeley successfully launched Eureka-1, UC Berkeley‚Äôs FIRST liquid bi-propellant rocket, becoming one of the select few collegiate teams in the world to accomplish such a monumental achievement. This comes at the conclusion of 3 years of development of our custom engineered propulsion system, avionics stack, simulation software, and aerostructure ‚Äî all designed and validated in-house by Berkeley‚Äôs brightest engineers. Despite the successful launch, the vehicle was not recovered successfully. But we are not deterred ‚Äî we see this as an exciting avenue to improve our methods and create an even better launch vehicle. We can‚Äôt wait to get to work next semester designing and validating our new system with ice-cold cryogenic flows, jaw dropping static fires, and heart stopping launches‚Ä¶ so stay tuned! Finally, a few words of gratitude. Thanks to our incredibly hard working team for their time and dedication to this project. Thanks to the family, friends, and sponsors who have supported us every step of the way. Thanks to everyone who tuned in to our livestream and for making this community so exciting to be apart of. We owe unlimited amount of gratitude to the SEB alumni who started us on this journey. We wouldn‚Äôt be where we are today without them. As always, blue skies and bright stars üöÄ","time":"8mo","title":"Space Enterprise at Berkeley"}]

name: CX Skills
location: Suite 591/585 Little Collins St, Melbourne, AU
about: CX Skills provides a range of training courses from beginner to advanced level for contact centres, customer service and customer experience employees. We partner with industry experts to bring you global best-practices and our courses are available for online delivery through either live, facilitaed courses or self-paced modules. We also offer onsite training options although with the myriad of COVID complications it is somewhat difficult to plan ahead with any real certaintity at the moment! Our courses are available publicly (so you can purchase a ticket for just one person through to a whole team) and we also have private courses available that are just for your employees. We currently have over 30 different courses available and we can also custom-design a program if you can't find an existing course to suit your needs. Popular courses include: - Contact Centre Management Fundamentals - Introduction to Contact Centre Management - Short booster courses for phone based customer service and sales roles - Introduction to Customer Experience (CX) - CX Management Fundamentals (doubles as the exam preparation for the CCXP certification) - How to Monitor and Coach call centre employees - How to Manage and Lead call centre employees - Managing Difficult Customers - Stress Management for customer service workers - Resilience training for customer service workers - Email Customer Service - Live Chat Customer Service - Workforce Optimisation - Plus lots more! Visit the website for all our available courses.

name: Law Reform Commission of Ireland
location: Dublin, IE
about: Our mission is to keep the law under independent, objective and expert review, to make recommendations for law reform and to make current law accessible for all. We work to improve and simplify the law through both our law reform and access to legislation activities. Our law reform proposals are first developed in Consultation Papers. These examine the law and set out questions on possible changes to the law. We then invite submissions on possible changes to the law, consulting widely. Submissions received help to inform our final analysis and recommendations that are published in our Reports. Many of our proposals have led to changes in Irish law. We also make existing legislation more accessible through three resources: 1. The Legislation Directory, which tracks all amendments made to legislation. 2. Revised Acts, which are administrative consolidations of all post-2004 Acts (excluding the Finance Acts and the Social Welfare Consolidation Act 2005) and approximately 170 pre-2005 Acts. 3. The Classified List, which categorises and presents legislation by subject matter, to make it easier for users to find the law in a particular area.

updates: [{"comments_count":8,"likes_count":141,"text":"We have published a Consultation Paper on Third-Party Litigation Funding. Third-party litigation funding occurs when a third party, who is otherwise unconnected to a party to a legal dispute, funds the resolution of that dispute in return for a share of any monetary remedy obtained. Assigning a cause of action means selling the right to sue to another person or entity. The law in Ireland currently prohibits both the funding of legal cases by outside parties who do not have a legitimate and independent interest in the dispute, subject to certain exceptions, and the assignment of a ‚Äúbare‚Äù cause of action. In light of the evolving legal and policy context for third-party funding, the Commission concluded that it was appropriate to publish a Consultation Paper setting out the current position in respect of the regulation of third-party funding and on the assignment of causes of action and to seek views on the matter. A core tension with third-party funding is the commodification of justice. Would legalising such funding promote this, or would it improve access to justice and improve equality of arms between parties to a dispute? Other questions considered in the Consultation Paper include: ‚öñ Whether third-party funding could address an inconsistency in the law, whereby corporate entities can effectively engage in third-party funding under another name by issuing shares or transferring ownership of the company to fund its participation in dispute resolution; ‚öñ Whether third-party funding might encourage the bringing of vexatious disputes; and ‚öñ Whether third-party funding could increase legal costs and the price of insurance premiums. We welcome your views and comments on the Consultation Paper, by 3 November 2023. More details are available on the Law Reform Commission‚Äôs website, www.lawreform.ie .","time":"3w","title":"Law Reform Commission of Ireland"},{"likes_count":7,"text":"T√° √°r nInt√©irneacht Taighde Dl√≠ Chothromais 2023 ag druidim chun deiridh. Our aim is to increase diversity in law by providing opportunities for law students who come from socio-economically disadvantaged backgrounds or have disabilities. In partnership with the Office of the Attorney General, the Office of the DPP and the Chief State Solicitor's Office, the internship has expanded this year to create exceptional learning and networking opportunities across all of those organisations. We have been supported by The Bar of Ireland, Law Society of Ireland, Courts Service, Houses of the Oireachtas and Victim Support at Court (V-SAC). We have opened the interns‚Äô eyes to the extensive array of opportunities available in law, in research and in public service. We have coached and mentored them on how to access those opportunities, culminating in a careers event yesterday. It included presentations by staff of the Office of the DPP on job applications and interviews, followed by a wide range of speakers who highlighted a variety of career options, particularly in the public sector, to provide inspiration and guidance for the interns as they start their careers. We are very grateful to Eleanor Leane, Legal Aid Board; Gareth Noble, KOD Lyons; Katie Mannion, Irish Refugee Council; Christopher Campbell, Department of Foreign Affairs, Ireland Affairs, and Elaine Cahill, Competition & Consumer Protection Commission (CCPC) for so generously sharing their time and wisdom. To mark the end of this year‚Äôs programme, the interns were addressed by Maureen Noonan, legal intern at the Law Reform Commission; by Mr Justice Frank Clarke, President of the Law Reform Commission; by Rossa Fanning SC, Attorney General; by Catherine Pierse, Director of Public Prosecutions; and by Maria Browne, Chief State Solicitor, who all remarked on the value of the initiative for both the interns and the bodies hosting them, and on the importance of improving access to opportunities for students from underrepresented backgrounds. Maureen Noonan said: ‚ÄúA highlight of the internship for me was getting an insight into the legal public sector. I think this is a rare opportunity for a recent graduate and making such an internship specifically for people from an access background is something which is very special and greatly appreciated. The connections I made are invaluable.‚Äù President Clarke spoke of the importance of a judiciary that is representative of society, and on the need for schemes like this one, because without diversity in the legal profession we cannot have a diverse judiciary. The internship programme has been a great success, not only in the stated aim of promoting diversity in law, but it has also been a triumph of interagency collaboration. It has had a ripple effect of goodwill and positivity, and we hope it will inspire the interns to themselves promote the access mission when they are in a position to do so. During this process, CO2 is captured before it enters the atmosphere and is then transported and stored in geological formations after separation from #naturalgas. The Oil and Gas industry is using new solutions to reduce its carbon #emissions, and this is exemplified by the initiative undertaken by Qatar Energy, of building new facilities for #CO2 sequestration and enhanced oil recovery (EOR). With water contained in the CO2-rich stream, a gas dehydration technology is required to remove water #vapor to mitigate the risk of pipeline corrosion. The key is based on TEG technology, which absorbs the water contained in the CO2-rich stream counter-currently, utilizing liquid triethylene glycol as its dehydrating agent to pull out water from a stream of CO2 flowing over it. A major benefit of using a TEG dehydration unit is the ability to recycle the drying fluid by removing #glycol from the gas stream for processing so that it can be purified and reused. name: Genetics & Applications
location: Ulica Zmaja od Bosne 8, Sarajevo, Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina 71000, BA
about: Genetics and Applications (G&A) is the official journal of the Institute for Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology, University of Sarajevo. It is envisaged as an international journal issued twice a year in print and online format, publishing peer-reviewed articles of novel and significant discoveries in the fields of basic and applied genetics. Special issues or supplements may also be produced from time to time upon agreement with the Editorial Board. Topics covered within Genetics and Applications (G&A) include: molecular genetics, cytogenetics, plant genetics, animal genetics, human genetics, medical genetics, population and evolutionary genetics, conservation genetics, genomics and functional genomics, genetic engineering and biotechnology, and bioinformatics. Authors are encouraged to submit complete, unpublished, original works that are not under review in any other journals. Acceptable papers are those that gather and disseminate fundamental knowledge in all areas of genetics.
specialties: molecular genetics, cytogenetics, plant genetics, animal genetics, human genetics, medical genetics, population and evolutionary genetics, conservation genetics, genomics and functional genomics, genetic engineering and biotechnology, and bioinformatics

name: Somato Publications

about: Somato Publications is an International Scientific and Scholastic Publisher that affiliates the Open Access Publications to make science widely available and benefit the scientific society by disseminating teaching and research on a global scale. Somato publishes scholarly articles subject to high-level peer review by eminent scientists. We follow ethical policies & standards to ensure high-quality scientific works and are freely accessible online. Somato Journals helps research scholars and other healthcare professionals to make new discoveries, improve their research strategies. OPEN ACCESS JOURNAL: Somato Publications is an open access publisher where the published articles are freely accessible to all the readers throughout the world without any subscription charges. Authors can retain the copyright of their work by licensing it under the Creative Commons Attribution License. Articles can be reused or redistributed by the authors without restriction unless the original work is correctly cited. PEER REVIEW: Somato Publications follow rapid double-blinded peer review process where author and reviewer details are maintained confidential. Once the article has been submitted to the journal, it will be assigned to an editorial board member for further peer review process. An editor will check whether the article submitted is within the scope of the journal and invite reviewers based on the area of expertise. Once the reviewer's comments are received it will be notified to the author to make necessary amendments. Post submission of the revised manuscript by authors will again be sent back to the reviewer to check the amendments, upon which the final decision for acceptance will be taken by the editor. PUBLICATIONS ETHICS: Articles published under Somato Publications follow COPE-Community of Publication Ethics. Authors, reviewers, and editors are instructed to follow publication ethics to maintain the journal integrity.
specialties: Scientific Publications, Open Access Journals, and Scholastic Publisher

updates: [{"likes_count":9,"text":"Last month, Assisi‚Äôs CEO Jacqueline, and Project and Engagement Officer Issy, travelled to Ngawi in Indonesia to meet our partner, Dreamdelion. about: Jewish Vocational Service (JVS) was founded in 1938 during the Great Depression to assist Jewish immigrants and refugees struggling to enter the American workforce and support their families. Today, JVS is among the oldest and largest providers of adult education and workforce development services in Greater Boston, serving a diverse clientele representing over 90 nations, and speaking 50 languages, and helping people secure financial independence through educational and employment services. With over 80 years of demonstrated excellence in workforce development, JVS has a reputation for continuous innovation, building person-centered and performance-based models to improve outcomes and increase programmatic effectiveness. Last year, JVS empower 16,000 individuals, including immigrants, refugees, people with disabilities, and older workers, to build their skills, advance their education, and build meaningful careers. JVS partners with over 1,300 area employers to help fill vacancies and provide the education their employees need to ascend their career ladders.

about: Luke Fry Architecture and Interior Design creates design-led properties that are refined, sophisticated, purposeful and relevant. Integral to our company values is the use of long-lasting materials such as brick, stone, concrete and timber that stand the test of time. We know it can take a village to achieve the best possible results and are committed to using only the very best professionals in their fields. Steered by Architect & Interior Designer Luke Fry, the company has longstanding relationships with specialist consultants and local councils and is committed to a delivering a smooth residential design and build process. Harnessing good design is a collaborative process and we work closely with all clients from conception to completion. Luke Fry Architecture & Interior Design was founded 8 years ago with the goal to design projects that foster a healthy, highly functional environment which creates a tailored experience that is connected to lifestyle. Enriching interaction rather than segregation is integral to the design approach. Based in Melbourne and Mansfield, our projects reach beyond the city limits to coastal, country, and alpine areas. We weight architecture and interiors equally to create holistic outcomes. A full service firm, we recognise the realities of everyday living and formulate interior identities that are highly-personalised, beautiful and easy to live with. Our expert team of interior designers and architects work closely to ensure all soft furnishings and decorative elements are in sync with the function, durability and aesthetic of the built in components. We champion products and pieces with integrity, longevity and the utmost style. We offer all-inclusive packages for loose furniture, lighting and art. Our connections to local makers and time-honoured relationships with leading brands and suppliers are invaluable resources when curating the pieces necessary for a unique and successful outcome.

updates: [{"text":"Four Colorado Laws Protecting Employees Who Discuss or Compare Wages Patricia S. Bellac, Esq., June 14, 2023 Within the last twenty years, laws have been enacted to encourage wage transparency and decrease the wage ‚Äúgaps‚Äù or differences, between genders and between whites and racial minorities. These new laws protect employees‚Äô right to discuss and compare wages and prohibit retaliation against employees who engage in those discussions. 1. Amendments to the Colorado Anti-Discrimination Act. Since 2008, it has been an unfair employment practice to discharge discipline, discriminate against, coerce or in any way intimidate threaten or interfere with an employee or other person because the employee inquired about disclosed compared or otherwise discussed the employees‚Äô wages. It is also an unfair labor practice to require an employee to disclose their past salary history as a condition of employment. C.R.S. ¬ß 24-34-402(1)(i). A person who participates in, or ‚Äúaids or abets‚Äù an unfair employment practice may also be liable under this act. In a more recent decision, Bonidy v. Vail Valley Center for Aesthetic Dentistry, P.C. (Colo. App. 2012), the Colorado Court of Appeals held that Colorado‚Äôs Minimum Wage Order, which is a document issued by Colorado‚Äôs Department of Labor and Employment on an approximately annual basis, articulates an important public policy upon which such a claim may be based. 2. Wrongful Discharge in Violation of Public Policy. An employer who discharges an employee because that employee asserted her right to receive compensation may be liable under the common law tort of wrongful discharge in violation of public policy. Hoyt v. Target Stores, 981 P.2d 188, 191 (Colo. App. 1998). 3. Colorado‚Äôs Equal Pay for Equal Work Act. Effective January 1, 2021 (January 1, 2022 for smaller employers), the Colorado Equal Pay for Equal Work Act (‚ÄúEPEWA‚Äù) forbids retaliation against employees who compare compensation and also prohibits employers from using salary history to determine pay. The EPEWA also requires wage transparency in job postings, i.e. requires an employer to provide the pay or pay range, in job postings and other employee recruiting documentation. 4. National Labor Relations Act. Under the National Labor Relations act, it is an unfair labor practice for an employer to interfere with activities and discussions amongst employees regarding wages, working conditions, hours of employment, and other terms and conditions of employment. The law expressly protects, ‚Äúconcerted activities‚Äù on these topics. Employee handbooks, offer letters, and separation agreements may not preclude employees from exercising these rights. Accordingly, provisions and employment documents that prohibit employees from disparaging the company or sharing company secrets should be modified to carve out employee rights of discussion in this area.","time":"1mo","title":"Patricia S. Bellac Law Firm, LLC"}]

name: Technical Applications Unlimited, Inc.
location: 425 Pierce Ave., Suite 303, Cape Canaveral, FL 32920, US
about: Technical Applications Unlimited, Inc. is a diversified professional services and product development company. We are a small business success story of the Florida-NASA Business Incubator program. TAU has outstanding experience in human space flight launch site design engineering, applied research and advanced technology development, computer and information systems, chemistry and chemical engineering, and other technical services. TAU maintains an expansive network of consulting employees who average more than 30 years of experience in mission critical electrical/electronic, mechanical, structural, gases/fluids, communications, environmental, chemical, and quality and safety engineering. These resources enable rapid response from genuine experts on an efficient basis. TAU has commercialized NASA technology that was initially conceived at Kennedy Space Center in support of the human space flight program. We have produced the Optical Fallout Monitor instrument that measure surface contamination accretion involving contaminants as small as 10 micros. Our advanced capability to produce custom instrumentation in low volumes to meet niche requirements is well-developed, diversified, and highly responsive.
specialties: Mission critical system design, development, and integration, Software, database, and website design and development, Chemical, optical, and electronic instrumentation, Applied research and technology development, and Communication and security systems

name: International School Jobs
location: The Broadgate Tower, 20 Primrose Street, London, London EC2A 2EW, GB
about: Established in 2007, InternationalSchoolJobs.com is a specialist jobs board aimed at the education sector. In particular we work with British and American International Schools, and teachers who want to teach abroad, including those coming to the UK to teach. Our customers include UK state schools, and privately owned and government run schools across the world. Owned and run by recruitment and education professionals, we aim to put international schools worldwide in touch with the best teachers seeking overseas teaching jobs. InternationalSchoolJobs.com offers international teaching vacancies in a range of subjects and locations and gives employers a very cost-effective way of quickly and simply recruiting for their schools. Employers can post job adverts direct on the site that are then syndicated to ensure the widest possible reach. Direct access to the candidate profile database is also available given employers the chance to approach suitable candidates based on their own search criteria. Using a variety of marketing strategies international school jobs ensures the widest audience for our customers' job vacancies. We target only fully qualified certified teachers ensuring that advertised positions are relevant to our audience and employers are not bombarded by applications from unsuitable candidates. For teachers who want to teach abroad we offer a free service where you can apply for jobs on line, receive alerts about suitable posts, and allow International School employers to search your resume online and contact you directly with teaching jobs abroad. The site is constantly evolving and we are always happy to hear feedback, good or bad, from our customers. Please feel free to get in touch with any comments by emailing admin@internationalschooljobs.com

about: AAA Holding Group Ltd. (AHG) represents the first huge and most significant milestone in British investment in Iraq, as we have strategically diverted our focus to invest in the growth and development of the Iraqi agricultural sector and far away from the oil and gas sectors. We are proud to be recognized as an active member of the Fertilizer Institute (TFI), a global body that advocates for responsible and sustainable fertiliser practices. In line with our commitment to quality and excellence, our company has obtained two prestigious certificates, ISO 14001 and ISO 9001. These certifications attest to our adherence to internationally recognized environmental and quality management standards, respectively. The company's Investment Capital is 550,000,000 million USD, with a Working Capital of approximately 450,000,000 million USD. Notably, our Gross Turnover is estimated to be around 750,000,000 million USD. At Phosphatic Fertilizers, we recognize the critical importance of using the right fertiliser to enhance the productivity of the soil and crops. We bring extensive agronomic experience and agricultural insights to maximize yields and elevate the standard of crops. We are also passionate about creating ideal farming conditions that lead to exceptional results, within a short period of time. We have a seamless flow of nitrogenous fertilizers and minerals to the soil, which increases the potency of crops and generates a flush of favorable produce, leading to exponential growth. Our resilience and dedication to supporting farming communities and feeding millions speak volumes about our commitment to sustainable agriculture practices. We continuously embrace modern inventions and invest in technological advancements to ensure that we provide our customers with the best possible solutions.
specialties: Fertilisers , Phosphates , Urea , and SSP
updates: [{"comments_count":1,"likes_count":8,"text":"AAA Holding Group‚Äôs New Production Line to Boost Iraqi Agriculture with a Capacity of 1 Million Tons Per Annum BAGHDAD, July 19, 2023 - AAA Holding Group, a pioneering global enterprise, has revealed its ambitious plans to bolster Iraq‚Äôs agricultural sector. The group is set to extend and expand its manufacturing plant in Iraq with a new Diammonium Phosphate (DAP) production line capable of producing a staggering 1 million tons per annum. DAP, a major source of phosphorus and nitrogen, is a crucial nutrient for the growth of a diverse range of crops. The projected capacity of the new production line stands to revolutionize the Iraqi agricultural landscape and self-sustain the nation‚Äôs fertilizer needs. Beyond the substantial boost to the domestic fertilizer supply, the project also entails significant civil engineering works. AAA Holding Group is working meticulously to secure materials, workforce, and manage timelines to ensure a successful execution of this expansion. The company is working in close collaboration with local government officials and stakeholders. Together, they aim to meet all regulatory requirements and secure the necessary permits for the project. AAA Holding Group acknowledges the potential environmental risks posed by DAP production, which involves the use of sulfuric and phosphoric acids. The company has committed to implementing robust waste management systems and disposal procedures to minimize environmental impact. AAA Holding Group‚Äôs substantial investment signifies a bold step forward in bolstering Iraq‚Äôs agricultural productivity. With the planned production capacity of 1 million tons of DAP per annum, the project is set to create a ripple effect, enhancing food security and boosting the national economy. In a related development, a sister company of AAA Holding Group has announced its intention to invest $4 billion in phosphate mining in the western regions of Iraq. This landmark investment further highlights the group‚Äôs commitment to bolstering the country‚Äôs agricultural sector. Phosphate is a key raw material for Diammonium Phosphate (DAP) production. Securing a local supply chain by investing in phosphate mining could significantly streamline the group‚Äôs DAP production process, reducing dependency on imported raw materials. This investment not only promises an economic boost to the regions where mining will occur but also aligns with the group‚Äôs strategy of enhancing domestic agricultural capabilities. With this substantial investment, the sister company aims to tap into Iraq‚Äôs rich phosphate reserves and contribute to creating a sustainable, self-reliant agricultural ecosystem in the country. about: Soul-Trackers Paranormal Investigations (STPI) was founded in September of 2001 by a team of veteran paranormal investigators in Pitman, New Jersey. STPI founder Jonathan Williams was an experienced veteran of paranormal investigation before the organization was founded. He along with several of the core team investigated along with Paranormal Spiritual Investigations (PSI), South Jersey Ghost Research (SJGR), New Jersey Paranormal Research (NJPR), and now Soul-Trackers (STPI). In the 25 years of study, Soul-Trackers core team has conducted hundreds and almost thousands of investigations all over the World. Investigations include: - East State Penitentiary, Philadelphia, PA - Phila. Historical Society, Philadelphia, PA - The Alamo, San Antonio, TX - Mt. Osore, Osorezan, Japan - Fort Mott State Park , Pennsville, NJ - Burlington County Jail , Mount Holly, NJ - Gettysburg National Park, Gettysburg, PA - Private Hangar, Private Military Base -Over 400 Private Residences and Businesses Throughout NJ, PA, DE, WI, IA -Over 500 Private and Public Cemeteries Throughout NJ, PA, DE, NY, SC, MI
specialties: Investigator, Head Investigator, and Director
slogan: Our mission is to provide compassionate and respectful assistance to those who have experienced hauntings.

ABOUT COSMO MUSIC:
Cosmo Music is one of the biggest and best musical instrument retail stores globally, providing sales, service, rentals, and lessons for all types of musical instruments in a one-of-a-kind, world class facility.

Learn more: https://cosmomusic.ca/pages/our-story.

We're not just a music store. In fact, we're much more than that. If you're looking to buy an instrument, rent some gear, improve your playing, get your instrument or gear back into top-working condition, help make your event a success, set-up the A/V for your organization, or even just a cool place to hang out and enjoy a coffee, we've got you covered.

A long history.
Established in 1968, over 50 years in the music business

You're with family.
Founded by Tom Hebert, family owned and operated

The single largest musical instrument store in North America.
60,150 sq ft store opened in May 2008

We know our stuff.
Over 200 employees including 23 repair technicians and 80+ highly qualified teachers

Unforgettable performances.
Home of the Cosmopolitan Music Hall venue

name: August Rose Health Center
location: 7477 Baltimore Annapolis Blvd, Glen Burnie, Maryland 21061, us
about:
Established in 2018, August Rose Health Center (ARHC) is a private, for-profit mental health and wellness organization. We are licensed in the State of Maryland and accredited by CARF (Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities). We provide mental health services, including Psychiatric Rehabilitation, to children over the age of 5, adolescents, and adults. Our services promote emotional well-being, recovery, and community inclusion.

We are committed to improving access to high-quality behavioral health services for all people in Maryland through the use of evidence-based practices and culturally responsive service delivery. We believe that all people should have access to quality behavioral healthcare. We are an organization that is founded on the values of empathy, compassion, cultural humility, respectfulness, and dignity in all interactions with the persons we serve, their families, our staff members, community partners, healthcare professionals, and other stakeholders at every level of our organization.
specialties: psychiatric rehabilitation, mental health, and counseling services

Proud to be one of the sponsors of the 2023 GOAT Youth Mental Health Expo! #mentalhealth #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealthawarenessmonth2023","time":"2mo 2mo","title":"August Rose Health Center"},{"time":"3mo"},{"likes_count":1,"text":"üîπThe Power of Connection: How Spending Time with Loved Ones Benefits Mental Health. üîπSpending time with loved ones can be a powerful form of self-care for mental health. Social support is essential for our well-being, and spending quality time with family and friends can help reduce feelings of isolation and loneliness. üîπWhen we connect with others, our brains release oxytocin, which is sometimes referred to as the \"love hormone.\" This hormone is associated with positive social interactions and can promote feelings of trust, bonding, and well-being. üîπSpending time with loved ones can take many forms, such as having a coffee date, going for a walk, watching a movie, or playing a board game together. It's about finding activities that allow you to connect and enjoy each other's company. üîπIn addition to providing social support, spending time with loved ones can also help us gain perspective on our problems and find new solutions to challenges. Give us a call and we'll help turn your ideas into reality...one stone at a time! 724-965-8142 #WorldChocolateDay #outdoorlivingideas #Fireplace #harmonyhardscape #smores","time":"2w Edited","title":"Harmony Hardscape"},{"likes_count":7,"text":"Harmony Hardscape & Landscape Supply July 2023 Blog Laying a Paver Patio/Sidewalk for a Stunning Hardscape Addition üè°‚öí Adding a paver sidewalk or patio to your outdoor space can transform it into a beautiful and functional area for relaxation. Whether you're a seasoned DIY enthusiast or a beginner, this article will provide you with instructions to successfully lay pavers. Create a stunning hardscape addition that will elevate the aesthetics and value of your outdoor space. Step 1: Planning and Design Start by envisioning the layout and purpose of your paver sidewalk or patio. Consider factors such as size, shape, and pattern, taking into account the existing landscape and architectural features. Create a detailed plan and calculate the quantity of pavers and base materials required for your project. Step 2: Site Preparation Prepare the area by clearing the space of any vegetation, rocks, or debris. Excavate the soil to the appropriate depth, allowing room for the base materials and paver thickness. Ensure proper slope and drainage to prevent water accumulation. Step 3: Base Installation Create a sturdy foundation by adding a base layer of crushed stone or gravel. Compact the base using a plate compactor or hand tamper to provide stability and prevent settling. Ensure the base is level and slopes away from structures for proper water runoff. Step 4: Edge Restraints Install edge restraints along the perimeter of your paver sidewalk or patio. This could be done using plastic or metal edging, concrete curbs, or other suitable materials. Edge restraints will help maintain the integrity and prevent the pavers from shifting over time. Step 5: Paver Installation Start laying the pavers from one corner, following the design pattern or layout you have planned. Use a rubber mallet to ensure each paver is level and properly seated. Maintain consistent joint spacing using spacers or your preferred method. Cut pavers as needed using a wet saw or paver splitter to fit around curves or edges. Step 6: Polymeric Sand Application After the pavers are installed, spread a layer of polymeric sand over the surface. Sweep the material into the joints, ensuring they are filled completely. Compact the sand with a plate compactor and use a water mist to activate the polymers in polymeric sand, creating a secure bond between the pavers. Step 7: Finishing Touches Clean the surface of the pavers, removing any excess sand or debris. Use a broom or leaf blower to sweep the area thoroughly. Apply a sealer, based on the paver company's recommendation, to enhance the color and protect the pavers from stains, UV rays, and weather damage. name: Alpha Phi Omega - Iota Phi
location: 1 Shields Ave, Davis, CA 95616, US
about: Alpha Phi Omega is a co-ed collegiate community service fraternity that strives to develop three cardinal principles: Leadership, Friendship, and Service. The Iota Phi chapter at UC Davis is among the largest in the nation, with members serving more than 10,000 hours in the Davis community each year. Leadership: Alpha Phi Omega develops the leadership skills of its members through shared leadership. Our members have the opportunity to serve as a chapter officer or to plan and execute any number of volunteer projects and social programs, as well as have the chance to participate in a variety of leadership development programs sponsored by Alpha Phi Omega. These programs consist of both online and in-person workshops and are presented by trained volunteer staff, to improve leadership skills for work within APO and in their professional lives. Friendship: The surest way to have a friend, is to be a friend. Service: The Iota Phi chapter of Alpha Phi Omega annually performs over 10,000 hours of service to Davis and the surrounding areas, working with schools, food banks, and community leaders. location: 30a Jessie St, Preston, Victoria 3072, AU
about:
The ACA is a not-for-profit, membership Association which disseminates information on corrosion and its prevention or control by providing training, seminars, conferences, publications and other activities.

Vision
Corrosion is managed sustainably and cost effectively to ensure the health and safety of the community and protection of the environment.

Mission

Assisting society to manage the impact of corrosion on asset durability.

about: We created Augmented Intelligence for wind to allow experts to optimise large fleets of wind turbines with minimum effort. We have captured the domain expertise of a team of industry experts and embedded this knowledge into fully automated analytics algorithms. This enables us to regularly check the health status of entire wind turbine portfolios, independent of turbine type or fleet size. We support our clients in developing new, digital processes to ensure that the resulting advisory information is converted into field actions, crossing the gap between data analytics and asset management. As a result, we achieve significant improvements in fleet performance, increased availability and reduced operating costs.

name: The Coral Triangle Initiative on Coral Reefs, Fisheries, and Food Security (CTI-CFF)
location: Jl. A.A. Maramis Kayuwatu, Kairagi II, Manado, North Sulawesi 95254, ID
about: The Coral Triangle Initiative on Coral Reefs, Fisheries, and Food Security (CTI-CFF) is a multilateral partnership of six countries working together to sustain extraordinary marine and coastal resources by addressing crucial issues such as food security, climate change and marine biodiversity. It is the first multilateral cooperation of its kind, one that focuses on food security through sustainable management of marine natural resources taking into consideration climate change impacts. The CTI-CFF is formed in 2009 and members include the governments of Indonesia, Malaysia, Papua New Guinea, Philippines, Solomon Islands and Timor-Leste (the ‚ÄòCT6‚Äô) representing the custodians of the Coral Triangle area. They adopted the CTI Regional Plan of Action (CTI RPOA) which is a strategic action plan with five goals: (1) designation of effectively managed seascapes; (2) application of an ecosystem approach to fisheries management; (3) establishment of a fully functional marine protected area system; (4) strengthening climate change adaptation and resilience; and (5) improving the status of threatened marine species.
specialties: Food Security, Multilateral Parnership, Marine Conservation, Marine Protected Area, Ecosystem Approach to Fisheries Management, Seascapes, Climate Change Adaptation, Threatened Species, Women Leaders' Forum, and Coral reefs

Origina is the world's leading independent third-party software maintenance and support provider for IBM software. Customers enjoy 24x7x365 customer support tied to a binding Service Level Agreement (SLA) which delivers response times as quickly as 30 minutes from when an issue is raised.

name: Colorado School of Mines
location: 1500 Illinois St, Golden, CO 80401, US
about:
Colorado School of Mines is a public research university devoted to engineering and applied science. It has the highest admissions standards of any public university in Colorado and among the highest of any public university in the U.S.

Mines has distinguished itself by developing a curriculum and research program geared towards responsible stewardship of the earth and its resources. In addition to strong education and research programs in traditional fields of science and engineering, Mines is one of a very few institutions in the world having broad expertise in resource exploration, extraction, production and utilization. As such, Mines occupies a unique position among the world's institutions of higher education.

Since its founding in 1874, the translation of the school's mission into educational programs has been influenced by the needs of society. Those needs are now focused more clearly than ever before. The world faces a crisis in balancing resource availability with environmental protection and Mines and its programs are central to the solution.

Mines offers all the advantages of a world-class research institution with a size that allows for personal attention.
specialties: engineering, mathematics, earth, energy, environment, Economics, Geology, Physics, Technology, Research, Education, science, and Computer Science

Apply today or share this post with your network.","time":"1w","title":"Raw Revel"},{"likes_count":6,"text":"Regenerative Agriculture and Its Relationship with Sustainable Fashion Regenerative agriculture is a type of farming that focuses on restoring degraded soils, increasing biodiversity, and enhancing ecosystem services. It is based on ecological principles and practices that mimic nature and promote its regeneration. Regenerative agriculture has many benefits for the environment, such as sequestering carbon, reducing greenhouse gas emissions, improving water quality, and supporting wildlife habitats. One of the industries that can benefit from regenerative agriculture is fashion. Fashion is one of the most polluting and wasteful industries in the world, consuming large amounts of water, energy, and chemicals, and producing huge amounts of textile waste and emissions. According to the United Nations, the fashion industry is responsible for 10% of global carbon emissions, 20% of global wastewater, and 85% of textiles that end up in landfills or incinerators every year. Regenerative fashion is a term that refers to clothing and accessories that are made from fibers and materials that are grown or sourced through regenerative agriculture. This means that the production of these fibers and materials does not harm the environment, but rather enhances it. Some examples of regenerative fibers and materials are organic cotton, hemp, linen, wool, silk, alpaca, cashmere, and leather. Regenerative fashion aims to create a circular economy for the fashion industry, where nothing is wasted and everything is reused or recycled. It also aims to support the livelihoods and well-being of the farmers and workers who produce the fibers and materials, as well as the communities and cultures they belong to. Regenerative fashion is not only about making clothes that are good for the planet, but also good for the people. Regenerative agriculture and regenerative fashion are part of a larger movement to transform our relationship with nature and each other. They offer a vision of a more sustainable, ethical, and beautiful future for the fashion industry and the world.","time":"2w","title":"Raw Revel"},{"likes_count":4,"text":"FASHION FACTS SERIES - Fact 03 Fashion might seem a small player in this emergency on Climate Change - This statement could not be further from the truth. name: The McDonald Group, Inc.
location: P.O. Box 730, Arlington Heights, IL 60006, US
about:
Thank you.  Do visit us: www.McDonaldGroupInc.com.

For 50 years we have been partnering with manufacturers and dealers to improve market share, profitability,  absorption rate and customer retention. 

Walter J. McDonald's latest book, "Achieving Excellence in Dealer/Distributor Performance," is now on Amazon.com, receiving praise from business leaders in North America, Europe and The Far East. 

If you sell and service machinery in the heavy construction equipment, forklift, fire apparatus, heavy duty truck, forestry equipment, utility, municipal and environmental, farm power and compact construction equipment industries, you are in our wheelhouse.

Our primary strengths are in 
* Marketing and business strategies for equipment manufacturers and dealer organizations.
* OEM field sales and dealer operations management training for district sales managers.
* Dealer management training for equipment sales managers, parts and service operations, rental and used equipment mangers, aftermarket marketing and customer service and retention.
* Dealer selling skills training and development.
* End user customer satisfaction assessments to determine competitive awareness and comparisons.

Our highly-qualified senior professional staff maintains a broad portfolio of resources and capabilities. Our industry-specific problem-solving experiences cover a broad spectrum of distribution management challenges both for manufacturers and dealers.  

Common client issues include:
Where should we take our dealer business and how?
How do we gain market share and still improve dealer absorption rate?
What are the key leverage points to improve  aftermarket operations and profitability?
How can we best apply and implement best industry practices and high-profit performance benchmarks? 
How do we make our machinery and aftermarket sales personnel more effective and competitive?
How should we best negotiate the challenges and opportunities of dealer consolidations?
specialties: Marketing and Business Strategy, Dealer Management Training, Aftermarket Marketing, Operations Improvement, OEM Dealer Development Support, Machinery, Aftermarket Selling Skills, Strategic Pricing, Mergers, Acqisitions, and Best Practices and Performance Benchmarks
slogan: We are the Global Leader in Industrial Machinery and Equipment Dealer Management Development.

name: Katie Woods Therapy
location: Lymm, Warrington wa13, GB,Tarporley Road, Stretton, Warrington, England WA4 4, GB
about: Having experienced trauma first hand when I was 14 years old, I understand the importance of having the right help and support through the difficult times and so this is where my passion lies. If you are considering therapy please take a moment‚Ä¶ Talking about painful and difficult subjects can be daunting and uncomfortable. It takes courage and strength to share this. It is my role to offer you a safe and supportive space, taking time to build trust and honesty between us. I work from the Person-Centred Approach which means no advice will be given and I won‚Äôt push or pull you in any direction. We will go at the your pace. I believe and trust that you will go wherever you need to. Empathy is very important to me. I acknowledge that everyone is different and I strive to understand each individual. I feel privileged to be invited into your life, let me stand in your shoes and appreciate your world. The therapeutic relationship between you and myself is key. To have someone who you are able to relate to is extremely valuable. I also work creatively, using Person-Centred Expressive Art Therapy. This can be beneficial in allowing us to freely express our feelings when we don't have the words to explain. Art therapy is your choice and can be used for whole or part sessions. This can be discussed in more detail depending on your preference. Therapy helps. It is your space be true and open, to try and understand what and why you are feeling this way. This in turn can help to restore your calmness. I believe the Person-Centred approach is the best tool to rebuild trust in yourself, and allow you to ultimately become your true self.
specialties: Anxiety, Depression, Loss and Grief, Loneliness, Low Self Esteem, Trauma, Anger, Chronic Pain, Life Changes, Personal Development, and Suicidal Thoughts
slogan: I am a fully qualified and compassionate Person-Centred Counsellor. Experienced in working with young people and adults.

name: Hailsham Creative
location: Hayreed Lane, Wilmington, Polegate, East Sussex BN266RR, GB
about: A design company that likes to bring out the creative side in its clients. We work WITH (not for) clients, collaborating and helping them to maybe see things another way - and there's nearly always another way!` We like the variety and energy we get working with small, medium and large businesses. We love to work with people that are equally as enthusiastic and committed as we are to doing things the right way, or a different way. We definitely work best with people that we like. We live and work in the middle of the Sussex countryside with a dog called Megan, who very much enjoys covering herself with fox poo for some reason (what's that all about?), two cats - one of whom is currently recovering from a skiing injury and the other is a reincarnation of Orson Wells. We are very old. Ancient in fact. Over 50. That is old, believe me, for graphic designers. Usually, designers of our vintage have inhaled so much Spray Mount and Magic Marker fumes, that brain and lungs have turned to a kind of grey sludge and congealed in our turn ups. We seem to have got away with it though and we're still creating. Creating what? Logos, branding, brochures, beautiful print work, magazine layouts, advertisements, exhibition displays, leaflets, posters, t-shirts, business cards, web sites, videos, music, painting, you name it! Seriously, you name it! That's one of the few good things about being old - you name it and we've probably done it already at some time. We even know what the internet is‚Ä¶ ‚Ä¶sort of!
specialties: Branding, identity, print, brochures, stationery, marketing, magazine design, packaging, and illustration
slogan: Branding, artwork, print or website creation, we'll give you the look you need without giving you kittens

about: Kiran Consulting Group (KCG) is a specialty consulting firm serving leaders in the industries of hospitality and tourism. Through unique simulation strategies, we help clients manage their large numbers of visitors, whether that be through line-management, exhibition flow and ticketing services. Using data-centric analysis, KCG redefines the differences between known and unknown, random and predictable, controllable and uncontrollable. In doing so, we drive dramatic improvements in our clients‚Äô ability to meet their customers‚Äô highest expectations. Since 1990, KCG has been called upon by operators of the world‚Äôs leading travel and tourist destinations to help solve their most challenging people-flow problems. Using KCG principles, we have developed predictive analytic solutions for arrival forecasting and labor scheduling for retail operations worldwide. As a social business, KCG works to better our cultural communities by working for investment, rather than purely profit. KCG‚Äôs work has allowed for industry leaders in culture and tourism to create unforgettable experiences for their guests, by managing all their visitor-related issues. From streamlining ticketing operations to controlling people flow through tight exhibition spaces, KCG works hard to create the right visitor experience for your needs. KCG has been an expert consultant for every major tourism industry since 1990, managing visitor flow through observation decks, fine art museums and UNESCO world heritage sites. Interested in finding out more about our services? Please feel free to reach out to us via email, LinkedIn, or by filling out our online form on our website.

about: An honors education at many universities is one-size-fits all. Not so at UAB. With almost 2,000 undergraduate students, the UAB Honors College offers two curricular options: Personalized Path and Specialized Programs. Students in the Personalized Path work with an advisor to create their own trajectory that includes honors seminars, core, and elective courses aligned with their unique interests and goals. The Specialized Programs offer structured curricula for interdisciplinary arts and sciences, science and technology, or global and community leadership. Whichever honors curriculum our students pursue, they benefit from a close-knit community and endless opportunities. The Honors College is dedicated to innovative courses, hands-on experience, service learning, and ‚Äî most importantly ‚Äî the individuality and diversity of our brilliant students.

updates: [{"time":"3w 3w","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"#traumaworkworks","time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"#traumaworkworks","time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"Children exhibit and array of behaviors everyday. Some we adore. Some not so much. Frequent misbehaviors can lead to the labeling of a child that stays with them. This labeling often occurs beginning in day care or kindergarten and can follow this child for the rest of their academic career. How often do you suppose kids get these labels from caregivers or teachers without a lot of investigation being done? Teachers rarely have the ability to do a deep dive on each child to ascertain their background because they are already overwhelmed. How often is a child diagnosed with ADD or ADHD and put on meds but the meds don‚Äôt really help because trauma at home is the problem? Mass produced education doesn‚Äôt shield the children from the trauma because it‚Äôs designed to cram them with knowledge and not create a safe space. Add to it the pitfalls of being in school and the traumas that can come from bullying and other social constructs it may be more than the child can bear and they simply drift. This is more common than we realize and it is heartbreaking. There is no easy fix but if we took a breath and asked some pertinent questions maybe not every child needs meds as an over correction. Maybe instead we love them as a village and dive a little deeper and help them do the work to get back on track and find their safe space. #traumaworkworks","time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"#traumaworkworks","time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"Trauma bonds are very real. They manifest and present themselves as maladapted behaviors that societally we accept as just how relationships are sometimes. Describing the relationship as really intense, hyper sexual, filled with arguing and making up constantly, mistrust of each other, Codependence etc are hallmarks of a trauma bond and not authentic connection. If we are in pain regularly in a relationship maybe we need to reassess what we want or how we give amd receive love. Sometimes folks describe a relationship as ‚Äúboring‚Äù and not having any spark or intensity. Maybe instead they have met someone that can provide them a healthy attachment that they simply don‚Äôt know how to receive. Knowing the differences between a trauma bond and healthy attachment can save us a tremendous amount of heartache and help us seek those attachments that fulfill and not further damage us. #traumaworkworks","time":"1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"time":"1mo 1mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"text":"#traumaworkworks","time":"2mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."},{"time":"2mo","title":"Admissions Alliance, Inc."}]

Semi-closed farming systems look much like conventional pens from above. But under the water, they have an opaque, impermeable outer barrier that surrounds the fish net. Waste and uneaten food cannot flow into the surrounding water, instead gathering at the bottom of the enclosure where it is collected, brought ashore, and treated. To replace the normal high flow of water through the net, clean, cold water is continuously pumped through the enclosure from deep below the surface. It's important to remember that terms like Australia and Aboriginal are colonial, not Indigenous. In other words, they are names that have been given by colonisers and not the names that First Nations people have traditionally used to refer to themselves. Generally, Indigenous people prefer to use their own names, like Bardi, Gadigal or Bundjalung, and to speak their own language. It is accepted that Australia is now an English-speaking country and so, if colonial terms must be used, most prefer Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, Indigenous Australians, First Peoples, First Nations or First Australians. Note the use of capital letters and remember, not all Indigenous people feel the same way or have the same preferences. name: Eco Nubia
location: Bigeh Island, Aswan, Aswan, EG
about: ECO Nubia is the new accomplishment of ECO Group. A place where guests can enjoy a unique experience with both Nature & History, in an Authentic and Genuine environment. It's our first Ecolodge of many to come soon, based on the concept of using old local community houses to be converted into Natural luxuries ecolodges, where both guests and local community can enjoy the Sustainable tourism experience. Location and houses are picked really carefully in order to provide the experience we promise, and allows you to "Release Your Inner Peace" while enjoying Nature & a unique Heritage. Our location is on Bigeh island: it is one of 3 islands located between the 2 Dams of Aswan governorate: The Aswan Dam and The High Dam, and also the nearest island to Philae temple. Because of its remoteness and lack of utilities & services, the island‚Äôs citizens left their homes on the islands since 40 years and now living in villages and cities around it. Still, they do have a dream of going back to their island and bringing its heritage back to life. We aim to help original inhabitants of the island to rebuild their houses, using the same old techniques of Nubian Architecture, in parallel to develop a complete utilities network and infrastructure (Water ‚Äì Sewage ‚Äì Electricity) in an eco-friendly way to protect the island‚Äôs natural heritage. As for job creation, we aim to add the island to the Egyptian ecotourism map, and introduce this unique type of tourism in the whole area around it, with all related services such as: lodging in Nubian houses, revive authentic Nubian food recipes and drinks, community center for local and visitors‚Äô events, Nubian handcrafts preservation.
specialties: Authentic Nubian Food, Eco-friendly rooms, Sandy Beach on the Nile, Multi Purpose Hall, Nubian Heritage, Eco-friendly Solutiuons, and Panoramic View of Philae Temple

about:
Bakker Brothers is specialized in the breeding, production and marketing of vegetable seeds. More than 95% of its sales is into export markets, with a special focus on Europe, Middle East and Africa.
 
The head offices are based in Noord-Scharwoude in the Netherlands. Bakker Brothers main breeding stations are in the Netherlands as well as in South Africa and Jordan. Production is done all over the world, depending on the most suitable production area.

Bakker Brothers is famous for its focus on bean varieties, but is also breeding and marketing vegetable crops like: tomato, pepper, eggplant, onion, carrot, pumpkin, cucumber and squash.This very wide range of products, with varieties for all kinds of climatic conditions, makes Bakker Brothers not only a serious and reliable partner, but also an interesting partner for customers who require the latest developments in breeding to meet their quality standards. Apart from breeding new varieties and hybrids, Bakker Brothers also produces all the generic varieties on our own stock seed, to ensure the highest quality and purity of these varieties.

Met deze uitkomsten zijn we heugelijk verrast en komen we een stap dichterbij het doel van onze missie. Eindigt het onderzoek hier? Nee zeker niet, dit is nog maar het begin! Inmiddels zijn we een jaartje verder en hebben wij niet stilgezeten. We blijven namelijk altijd opzoek naar nieuwe uitdagingen. Zo zijn we sinds enkele weken een nieuw project gestart. Met het team zijn we aan het onderzoeken wat er allemaal gedaan kan worden met de mosselschelp, n√° de consumptie van de mossel. Deze insteek is niet zonder reden. Het is namelijk een feit dat Zeeland een grote producent is op gebied van mosselproductie. Met miljoenen kilo‚Äôs per jaar kan men Zeeland als het epicentrum van Noordwest-Europa betitelen. Met deze miljoenenindustrie komt er ook een hoop afval vrij. Van de mossel wordt in totaal slechts 20% geconsumeerd. Deze 20% is namelijk het weekdier zelf. De schelp blijft over en tot op heden is er nog geen structurele oplossing voor. Al deze aspecten hebben ons aangespoord om te kijken op welke manier we de mosselschelp circulair kunnen maken. Om het te concretiseren gaan we onderzoeken hoe we de keramische industrie kunnen ondersteunen. Zo zijn we afgelopen week al van start gegaan met verschillende tests met onze specialisten in de keramiekbranche. Om dit onderzoek te realiseren hebben wij een uitbreiding in ons assortiment bedacht die in lijn ligt met ons doel: de duurzame Zeeuwse Mosselsok. Wat de Mosselsok extra uniek maakt, is dat deze gemaakt is van bamboe. De Mosselsok heeft hetzelfde patroon als de Zeeuwse Mosselboxershort. De opbrengsten van de sokken en de boxers zorgen voor de financiering van het onderzoek. Wij van DownUnder wear geloven dat elke vorm van support een enorme impact kan maken om dit onderzoek tot een succes te brengen. Een aantal dingen die u zou kunnen overwegen om ons hierbij te helpen: - Een kijkje nemen op onze website (www.downundershop.nl) - Overwegen of een van onze producten een mooie toevoeging is aan het kerstpakket van uw bedrijf - Dit bericht herplaatsen op LinkedIn - Uw vrienden, familie, collega's en kennissen vertellen over uw ervaring met ons bedrijf Wij hopen u met ons bericht ge√Ønspireerd te hebben en hopen dat u bereid bent ons te helpen bij het verduurzamen van de mosselindustrie. Wij zijn enorm dankbaar voor alle support en geloven dat elke vorm van steun een grote bijdrage kan leveren aan dit mooie doel. Team DownUnder #ondernemen #sustainable #studenten","time":"8mo","title":"DownUnder wear"}]

about: MAG & More has been involved in the field of magnetic neurostimulation for more than 15 years. Our focus lies on creating innovative products which fulfil the highest quality standards. We are truly commited to guarantee the satisfaction of our costumers with the quality, functionality and technology of our products and hence we provide our customers with service packages that offer the right solution for their individual requirements. Behind our innovative products stand highly motivated employees with a great deal of experience, who work with a strong team spirit to meet all the needs of our international clients. Our corporate headquarters and production facilities are in Bavaria, Germany. There, we continually develop modern concepts for stimulators, coils and other competences with the objective of providing patients who suffer from various neurological and psychiatric illnesses an alternative therapy with high clinical benefit that improves quality of life. MAG & More GmbH has been a privately managed company since its foundation. As a result, we are capable of acting independently in our future, investing and planning for the long term. MAG & More is a leader in the field of repetitive magnetic stimulation. We focus on the development and worldwide sale of high-quality medical technology ¬´Made in Germany¬ª. By providing highest quality products, we are consciously committed to satisfying our customers and towards contributing to the health of their patients. We are motivated daily by the challenge to be an innovative and cooperative partner for our customers and business associates. An emphasis in our philosophy is always on optimal customer support and respectful cooperation with all our customers and business associates.

name: River Ocean Cleanup (ROC)
location: Street P-01, Phnom Penh, KH
about: Cambodia has one of the fastest economic growth (7% annually) compared to countries in the Asia Pacific region due to political stability, increase in local and international investments and tourism. Despite the economic growth, new challenges are emerging for the country, including the amount of waste generation and the management of urban solid waste. The annual solid waste generation is approximately 3.65 million tons per year (2017) and increases between 10% to 15% every year. 48% of this solid waste is not collected and is therefore found on the streets, rivers, and ocean. Mismanaged wastes cause negative impacts on the health and well-being of citizens, water quality, marine lives, wildlife, the tourism industry and it also contributes to climate change. ROC‚Äôs strategy is to address the problem through the mobilization of the Cambodian population across the country to lead or join cleanup legacy trashes (especially plastic) on the ground, in the rivers and the ocean.

about: Come join us on a tropical haven called Mafia Island and help us build up a farming homestay. Help our foundation in supporting and teaching the local community. We are linked to a whale shark safari business and you will have opportunity to help with the safaris, doing organic gardening, converting our bungalow for budget accommodation and being part of an awesome community! You have the power to open up some amazing opportunities for local Mafian people with skills you don't even know are significant... Mafia Island is the main island situated in the Mafia Archipelago, it is one of a few places around the world where the Whale Sharks go against their natural instincts and remain all year round. Mafia is so blessed that is is a safe place for them to have and nurture their young, so why would they leave? The island is also home to the most beautiful and pristine marine park on the entire East African coastline, boasting coral reefs and underwater life that is unmatched in the region. This makes Mafia Island a hotspot for divers and snorkelling tourists from around the globe, if you join our vibrant team then we would love to share experiences such as these and more, doing it in local Swahili coast fashion. Our homestay is small (max 4 people capacity), super homely, safe and peaceful. We're located in a beautiful forest, the quiet neighborhood is friendly and welcoming, with the stunning beaches of Kilindoni, within 20 minutes walking distance. Travelers come to us in search of tranquility and nature, which there's plenty of all around our house. We keep our home farm very clean and we take the best care of our guests so that they feel like family. We are seeking bright minded and forward thinking individuals with skills in agriculture, permaculture, horticulture, we are also interested in people with skills in website design, social media management, business administration and marketing. We love people who are passionate about art, culture,
specialties: Tourism, Agriculture, Education, Culture, and Learning
